<biogHist>
<abstract>A supply authority is a document issued by the Department of Community Services Adoption Information Unit to people who are seeking adoption information. Supply authorities contain identifying details of all the parties at the time of the adoption: the adopted person, the birth parents and adoptive parents. The supply authority form then allows you to obtain further information, e.g. social and medical history, from adoption records. Before birth parents or adoptees can access information held by the Registry of Births, Deaths and Marriages, they must gain a supply authority. Fees apply.</abstract>
<h4>Adoptees who already have their Original or Amended Birth Certificate do not need to apply for a supply authority.</h4>
<p>Adoptees can use their original or amended birth certificate to obtain information from Community Services and other sources.</p>
<p>Further information about adoptions may be held by non-government adoption agencies, the Registry of Births, Deaths and Marriages, the hospital where the adopted person was born, and the Supreme Court. These agencies may also charge fees.</p>

</biogHist>
</description>
